# Drag-and-drop for lists and tables

## Default — flat and simple lists

Renderer **drag-and-drop reorder** in lists (**`QList`** / **`QItem`**, vertical settings rows, chip lists, non-tree non-**`QTable`** collections) → **[`vue-draggable-plus`](https://vue-draggable-plus.pages.dev/en/)** (`package.json`).

- **`VueDraggable`** + **`v-model`** on backing array, or **`useDraggable`** / **`v-draggable`** when list root not plain wrapper (e.g. Quasar list bodies).
- Dedicated **drag handle** (grip on **`QItemSection`**) via Sortable **`handle`** when rows also navigate/open menus on click.
- Persist new order via existing Pinia + IPC after drop; map indices to domain fields (e.g. **`sort_order`** on worlds).
- **Vertical tab strips** (e.g. **Project Settings** world/document-template tabs): **`vue-draggable-plus`** + **`src/scripts/faDragDrop/`** (**`buildFaVerticalDraggableTabsRootStyle`**, sortable options, drag cursor) + **`faVerticalDraggableTabs`** SCSS. TabList hosts: layout props (**`tabListWidthPx`**, **`tabPadding`**, **`tabTextAlign`**, **`tabJustifyContent`**, **`tabLabelTextTransform`**, **`tabLabelFontSize`**, **`dense`**) — **`types/I_faVerticalDraggableTabs.ts`**, [fantasia-drag-drop skill](../skills/fantasia-drag-drop/SKILL.md) **Vertical draggable tab strips**.

**Do not** add SortableJS, **`vuedraggable`**, **`vue-draggable-next`**, or ad hoc HTML5 **`draggable`** for list reorder unless maintainer documents narrow exception in review.

## Exception 1 — hierarchical trees (`@he-tree/vue`)

**Nested expand/collapse tree** → **`@he-tree/vue`** (`BaseTree` / **`Draggable`**) built-in DnD. **No** **`vue-draggable-plus`** on tree nodes.

See [fa-he-tree.mdc](fa-he-tree.mdc), [fantasia-he-tree skill](../skills/fantasia-he-tree/SKILL.md).

## Exception 2 — **`QTable`** row reorder

**`QTable`** row reorder → **`quasar-ui-q-draggable-table`** (**`v-draggable-table`**). Boot: **`src/boot/q-draggable-table.ts`**.

- Directive **`options.mode`**: **`'row'`** for row reorder (default column mode = column drag).
- **`onDrop(from, to)`** splices backing **`rows`**; library reports indexes only — does not mutate Vue state.
- **Row mode incompatible with `virtual-scroll`** on same table; non-virtual table or other UX for very large row sets.
- Column reorder: same directive **`mode: 'column'`** when product need arises.

**Do not** use **`vue-draggable-plus`** on **`QTable`** body rows.

## Out of scope (custom pointer sessions)

**Spatial** drag (movable floating windows, free-position panels) → feature **`src/scripts/`** pointer sessions (e.g. **`faFloatingWindowTitleDragPointerSession`**) — not list libraries above.

